title: We remember Che who was killed in 1967 and a baseball update | Opinion - Conservative
text:
(Before It's News)
Jorge Ponce joins me to talk about the 48th anniversary of Che’s capture and execution…..he left Cuba to start a revolution in Bolivia and was eventually capture……..a total failure at revolution became a revolutionary icon……a man who despised capitalism is now used to peddle capitalism, from T-shirts to airlines…….we will do an update of the Rangers-Blue Jays series and others……click to listen:
